description:
Set 1

Heaven Help The Fool, Sage And Spirit, Little Sadie, Monkey & The Engineer, It Must Have Been The Roses, Cassidy, Bird Song-> Ripple

Set 2

Jack Straw, Cold Rain & Snow, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Ramble On Rose-> Little Red Rooster, Brown Eyed Women-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 3

Don't Ease Me In-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Franklin's Tower-> Drums-> Fire On The Mountain-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Good Lovin', E: Uncle John's Band

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text:
Another Stellar Blue... ... 20 out of 20 stars.

absolutely wonderful!
Spectacular! An amazing show! I wish I had been there...

This is IMO the best aud of this show There are 3 good auds of this show, and I think this one has the richest sound.  First few acoustic songs are real quiet, and the rowdy NYC crowd makes their presence known.  But its all still very listenable.  I dont like the mix of the pre-FMs of this show, they lack some warmth, and are almost too harsh.  Id like to hear the multi-track copy the band has in the vault though.  That I would pay for.  In the meantime, enjoy this audience which winds up this historic, NYC run.

boot I've held other recordings much closer to my heart with little exclaim, and virtually no reason. this one arrives on my desk with no invitation, very little warning, I've never cared much for the decades that followed what majesty the seventies entitled. but it rounds the painting nicely anyway to visit something like this tape which has everything one might need without all of the luggage something messier might. I don't know what that is because again I have no idea what even this is...what I'm trying to say is thank you very much.
